188
00:20:59,940 --> 00:21:01,010
I don't know.

189
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,080
She had a bag full of 500ml water bottles.

190
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:04,920
Does she sell them?

191
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:07,350
Anyway, you know the typical middle-aged woman.

192
00:21:07,690 --> 00:21:09,520
Relentless and thick-faced.

193
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:11,260
She was pretty though.

194
00:21:11,620 --> 00:21:13,390
I bet she was popular back in the day.

195
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,130
- Find out about her. - Pardon?

196
00:21:18,260 --> 00:21:19,630
Come on, sir.

197
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,770
Because she's pretty?

198
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:23,870
You almost hit her in the street...

199
00:21:23,870 --> 00:21:25,140
and you want to ignore that?

200
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:26,900
What human does that?

201
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,610
- Is that how I taught you? - No, sir.

202
00:21:31,410 --> 00:21:33,010
I know nothing about her.

203
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:35,410
- I do. - Pardon?

204
00:21:35,780 --> 00:21:37,250
Her child goes to Jun Seo's school.

205
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:38,650
What? Really?

206
00:21:42,890 --> 00:21:46,490
(Convalescent Ward)

207
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:50,660
(Homeroom Teacher)

208
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:52,400
I keep asking Young Min,

209
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:55,100
but he won't say what happened.

210
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,310
Young Min won't say.

211
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:11,650
The meek and sweet little boy...

212
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:15,650
threw a chair at a kid.

213
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:21,190
And I completely forgot about that.

214
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:24,730
From last night until now.

215
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:29,070
I'm a bad mom, aren't I?

216
00:22:36,410 --> 00:22:37,840
It snowed.

217
00:22:40,610 --> 00:22:42,880
It snowed a lot. Maybe that's why.

218
00:22:46,150 --> 00:22:48,250
This season thing really gets to me.

219
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:54,830
I wish there were only one season,

220
00:22:55,890 --> 00:22:57,360
but there are four.

221
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:02,630
Each one of them is pretty and heart-fluttering.

222
00:23:05,070 --> 00:23:07,500
They come hand-in-hand with him.

223
00:23:09,770 --> 00:23:11,780
On some days, he comes with the wind.

224
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:15,010
On some days, he comes with the flowers.

225
00:23:16,650 --> 00:23:18,280
On some days, he comes with the rain.

226
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:27,520
When I close my eyes not to see him, I can remember him more vividly.

227
00:23:29,030 --> 00:23:31,330
When I drink because I feel so miserable,

228
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:33,530
he shows up in my dream without a warning.

229
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:38,970
He shows up every single day even when I don't do anything,

230
00:23:39,340 --> 00:23:41,410
so I couldn't live my life.

231
00:23:48,650 --> 00:23:49,780
No.

232
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,350
Actually,

233
00:23:57,690 --> 00:23:59,760
I could live because of his memories.

234
00:24:07,530 --> 00:24:10,900
I imagined us meeting again over hundreds of times.

235
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,010
But what happened yesterday...

236
00:24:15,010 --> 00:24:17,370
wasn't in any of the scenarios I thought of.

237
00:24:20,910 --> 00:24:23,380
Why did we have to meet again...

238
00:24:24,580 --> 00:24:27,080
when I was the most pathetic and miserable?

239
00:24:56,910 --> 00:24:58,980
They are my wife...

240
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:01,050
and my daughter.

241
00:25:02,290 --> 00:25:04,050
Aren't they beautiful?

242
00:25:17,170 --> 00:25:19,670
But it was nice seeing Jae Hyun again.

243
00:25:23,070 --> 00:25:24,370
That's why I can understand...

244
00:25:24,370 --> 00:25:26,340
how much pain you must be in, Dad.

245
00:25:50,100 --> 00:25:53,000
Sir, your wife is home.

246
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:06,350
Can we talk?

247
00:26:13,690 --> 00:26:15,960
Do you run a charity?

248
00:26:16,090 --> 00:26:19,030
I thought you already donated enough of your money.

249
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:20,260
What's your point?

250
00:26:20,260 --> 00:26:22,570
Who told you we would let this incident slide?

251
00:26:22,870 --> 00:26:24,800
Who said you could let that kid off the hook?

252
00:26:25,540 --> 00:26:27,700
Should I have put him in prison or something?

253
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:30,370
Of course. He attacked our son.

254
00:26:30,370 --> 00:26:31,740
It's nothing serious.

255
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:33,240
And he's still a kid.

256
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,210
It's worse because he's only a kid.

257
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:38,950
He's already violent toward other kids at that age.

258
00:26:38,950 --> 00:26:41,150
What if his aim was better and the chair hit our son?

259
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:43,020
Didn't you think about that?

260
00:26:43,020 --> 00:26:44,790
Check on Jun Seo first.

261
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,620
See if he made any mistakes.

262
00:26:46,620 --> 00:26:48,560
Even if he did, that doesn't matter!

263
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:50,090
I'm already annoyed...

264
00:26:50,090 --> 00:26:52,600
that he's going to school with my son for free.

265
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:54,830
We'll settle this? We won't press charges?

266
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,930
That will never happen!

267
00:26:57,130 --> 00:27:00,000
If you do this, you'll only ruin our son.

268
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,710
I heard a few things about the incident,

269
00:27:02,710 --> 00:27:03,740
so don't dismiss my decision.

270
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:26,360
Can we talk?

271
00:27:31,240 --> 00:27:33,900
I don't like beating around the bush. I'll cut to the chase.

272
00:27:33,970 --> 00:27:36,470
I want you to resign your position as the chairperson of our committee.

273
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:39,610
It won't be pretty if we object.

274
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:41,750
I want you to tell the school that you'll resign.

275
00:27:43,810 --> 00:27:45,650
I didn't take the position because I wanted to,

276
00:27:45,650 --> 00:27:47,420
so I can tell the school I'll resign,

277
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:49,720
but may I ask you why?

278
00:27:49,820 --> 00:27:51,560
I heard about Young Min.

279
00:27:51,820 --> 00:27:54,160
Well, it's not just about him.

280
00:27:55,260 --> 00:27:57,430
The problem is you.

281
00:27:58,860 --> 00:28:01,060
You lied to us more than I can count.

282
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,300
You're divorced.

283
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:06,070
I guess you don't need to disclose that since it's your personal life.

284
00:28:06,970 --> 00:28:08,670
But you're working at a supermarket.

285
00:28:08,670 --> 00:28:10,370
That's a bit appalling, you know.

286
00:28:11,140 --> 00:28:14,210
Another parent saw you doing a protest in front...

287
00:28:14,210 --> 00:28:15,980
of the supermarket headquarters.

288
00:28:16,250 --> 00:28:17,310
Was she wrong?

289
00:28:17,310 --> 00:28:19,620
Must I disclose my personal life...

290
00:28:20,150 --> 00:28:21,920
to you?

291
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:24,420
You shouldn't have deceived us at least.

292
00:28:24,820 --> 00:28:28,230
I'm sorry if you felt I deceived you.

293
00:28:29,130 --> 00:28:31,700
I didn't want to tell you because I didn't want you...

294
00:28:31,700 --> 00:28:33,730
to judge my son based on my decision.

295
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:36,800
Let's be honest. Weren't you embarrassed to tell us?

296
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:39,770
You already knew that you wouldn't...

297
00:28:39,770 --> 00:28:41,270
be able to socialize with us.

298
00:28:44,410 --> 00:28:46,480
That part is true.

299
00:28:46,610 --> 00:28:49,510
Dealing with school stuff and eating brunch at the hotel was too much.

300
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:52,320
This all worked out. I'll tell the school.

301
00:28:52,420 --> 00:28:55,020
Unbelievable. How could you be so brazen?

302
00:28:55,020 --> 00:28:56,020
Aren't you going to apologize?

303
00:28:56,020 --> 00:28:57,620
You must have forgotten already.

304
00:28:57,620 --> 00:28:59,290
I already did 30 seconds again.

305
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:15,170
(Lee Se Hun)

306
00:29:22,610 --> 00:29:23,880
What is it?

307
00:29:27,050 --> 00:29:28,920
Tell me what you couldn't tell me on the phone.

308
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:32,860
This is rude. You didn't even knock.

309
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:35,430
I keep my manners only to humans.

310
00:29:38,530 --> 00:29:41,160
Did something happen to Young Min?

311
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,070
No.

312
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:45,440
Really?

313
00:29:45,970 --> 00:29:48,170
- Nothing happened. - That's odd.

314
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:50,870
Why is his cell phone turned off then?

315
00:29:50,870 --> 00:29:52,140
It's been off for two days.

316
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:56,110
Didn't you call him?

317
00:29:57,810 --> 00:29:59,420
He called me with his friend's phone.

318
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:01,150
He said his phone was broken.

319
00:30:01,690 --> 00:30:03,720
I see. Is that so?

320
00:30:05,690 --> 00:30:08,290
If this is it, you should tell me on the phone.

321
00:30:09,490 --> 00:30:11,430
I can't see your eyes on the phone.

322
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:15,730
Our eyes can't lie.

323
00:30:20,740 --> 00:30:22,810
I will never come to your office again.

324
00:30:23,170 --> 00:30:25,440
You should try to find a way to tell if I'm lying or not...

325
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:27,040
through my voice.

326
00:30:42,660 --> 00:30:45,300
If you settle, your charge can get acquitted.

327
00:30:47,460 --> 00:30:49,130
I won't settle.

328
00:30:51,330 --> 00:30:54,200
If the court accepts you did this on purpose, you'll serve time...

329
00:30:54,670 --> 00:30:56,370
when you shouldn't serve time.

330
00:30:56,810 --> 00:30:59,980
It was neither an accident nor done in the heat of the moment.

331
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:02,580
He mocked the accident...

332
00:31:02,580 --> 00:31:04,510
and ridiculed my bereaved family.

333
00:31:04,780 --> 00:31:07,020
He didn't show any signs of remorse or repentance.

334
00:31:08,990 --> 00:31:10,120
I...

335
00:31:10,950 --> 00:31:12,990
intended to do it.

336
00:31:16,130 --> 00:31:18,200
I'm going to tell the world...

337
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:20,360
what he did.

338
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:42,950
The phone is turned off. You'll be directed to the voicemail box.

339
00:31:43,890 --> 00:31:46,120
(Homeroom Teacher)

340
00:31:49,530 --> 00:31:51,090
The receiver cannot be reached.

341
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:58,570
Termination is murder! Cancel the unfair dismissal!

342
00:31:58,570 --> 00:32:00,840
- Cancel! Cancel! - Cancel! Cancel!

343
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:02,570
Cancel the unfair dismissal!

344
00:32:02,570 --> 00:32:04,640
- Cancel! Cancel! - Cancel! Cancel!

345
00:32:04,710 --> 00:32:07,310
The management must wake up!

346
00:32:07,310 --> 00:32:09,550
- Wake up! - Wake up!

347
00:32:10,750 --> 00:32:11,850
Hey.

348
00:32:14,820 --> 00:32:16,550
It's about the woman you wanted me to look into.

349
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:18,720
Yes. What did you find out about her?

350
00:32:19,190 --> 00:32:20,820
She's divorced.

351
00:32:20,820 --> 00:32:21,990
She's divorced?

352
00:32:21,990 --> 00:32:23,390
Yes, three years ago.

353
00:32:24,090 --> 00:32:26,030
That can't be right.

354
00:32:26,030 --> 00:32:28,370
As of now, it's just her and her son on her family register.

355
00:32:28,370 --> 00:32:30,600
Does it mean she's raising her son alone?

356
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,270
Yes, it seems like it.

357
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:35,310
Then, what about her ex-husband?

358
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:37,670
Is he paying her alimony?

359
00:32:37,670 --> 00:32:39,540
He's a lawyer at a law firm.

360
00:32:39,540 --> 00:32:41,110
They had a divorce lawsuit.

361
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:42,910
In exchange for getting the custody of their son,

362
00:32:42,910 --> 00:32:45,280
she gave up on receiving alimony and child support.

363
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,620
How does she get by?

364
00:32:47,150 --> 00:32:48,290
Does she have a job?

365
00:32:48,290 --> 00:32:50,320
No, not really.

366
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,690
It looks like she has a few part-time jobs.

367
00:32:56,530 --> 00:32:59,160
(Make sure to turn on your headlights.)

368
00:33:32,130 --> 00:33:33,200
Yes, hello.

369
00:33:33,930 --> 00:33:35,800
Ms. Yoon. You called me earlier.

370
00:33:36,070 --> 00:33:39,340
Yes. Young Min's cell phone is turned off.

371
00:33:39,700 --> 00:33:41,200
I was worried if something happened to him.

372
00:33:42,040 --> 00:33:44,170
No, nothing happened. He was in all of his classes.

373
00:33:44,610 --> 00:33:45,610
Really?

374
00:33:46,940 --> 00:33:48,950
I'll tell Young Min to call you.

375
00:33:50,010 --> 00:33:52,380
Okay. Please tell him to call him.

376
00:33:53,220 --> 00:33:54,250
And...

377
00:33:55,290 --> 00:33:57,190
there's one more favor I wanted to ask you.

378
00:33:57,390 --> 00:33:58,620
Sure, go ahead.

379
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:03,060
If his father calls,

380
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:06,500
could you not tell him about the incident?

381
00:34:10,170 --> 00:34:11,470
I don't want him to worry.

382
00:34:13,140 --> 00:34:14,970
Okay. Thank you.

383
00:34:37,230 --> 00:34:38,960
What is it? Did I annoy you?

384
00:34:41,100 --> 00:34:44,530
I must have lost my mind when I hurt my head.

385
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:48,140
It's because of you, so I hope you understand.

386
00:35:16,200 --> 00:35:19,770
- When the dawn breaks - When the dawn breaks

387
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:23,610
- The red sun soars high - The red sun soars high

388
00:35:23,770 --> 00:35:27,110
- Our bloody heart turns into a rage - Our bloody heart turns into a rage

389
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:30,780
- And becomes a massive wave - And becomes a massive wave

390
00:35:30,910 --> 00:35:34,620
- Even when people are out to get us - Even when people are out to get us

391
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:36,850
- We will defeat them and become one - We will defeat them and become one

392
00:35:36,850 --> 00:35:39,420
And you must quickly decide what you plan to do...

393
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:41,660
with the temporary employees who have been protesting...

394
00:35:41,860 --> 00:35:43,430
for over a month now.

395
00:35:43,590 --> 00:35:46,300
What do you think I should do, Mr. Park?

396
00:35:46,300 --> 00:35:49,200
We didn't violate the contract.

397
00:35:49,570 --> 00:35:53,170
But they are arguing that the contract itself was unfair.

398
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:55,610
- I want us to stick to the law. - Put yourself in their shoes.

399
00:35:57,210 --> 00:36:00,110
Most of them are housewives in their 40s and 50s.

400
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:03,680
If we just terminate them at this day and age, they will...

401
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:06,020
start petitioning and cause quite a mess.

402
00:36:06,220 --> 00:36:08,220
Then, what do you suggest that we do?

403
00:36:08,220 --> 00:36:10,050
Just let them be.

404
00:36:10,590 --> 00:36:13,920
It looked like they were having fun. It's like they're on a picnic.

405
00:36:14,060 --> 00:36:17,130
Do you think they'll break down the door and barge in here?

406
00:36:17,830 --> 00:36:18,860
Right.

407
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,500
Talk to the legal team...

408
00:36:20,500 --> 00:36:22,370
and bring me a plan.

409
00:36:22,570 --> 00:36:25,600
Don't ask me questions like you're giving me a quiz.

410
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:27,700
Okay.

411
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:29,710
We'll pretend to negotiate the terms and stall time.

412
00:36:30,110 --> 00:36:31,570
And they'll be forced to disband.

413
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,710
Illegal labor disputes, occupying our building without permission,

414
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:36,110
obstruction of business, and so on.

415
00:36:36,810 --> 00:36:40,150
Gather all the evidence that could forcefully remove them.

416
00:36:41,180 --> 00:36:42,220
Yes, sir.

417
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:04,710
By the way, why aren't you getting married?

418
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:07,880
Wait, did you already get married once?

419
00:37:08,950 --> 00:37:12,350
I can't believe no one made a move on such a handsome man like you.

420
00:37:12,620 --> 00:37:14,750
- No way. - I'm sure he had a girlfriend.

421
00:37:15,750 --> 00:37:17,750
You couldn't choose because you had too many, right?

422
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:20,060
I liked a girl,

423
00:37:21,190 --> 00:37:22,960
but she didn't know for 25 years...

424
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:25,500
because she's like a horse at the racecourse.

425
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:30,800
Well, it's not that bad.

426
00:37:31,530 --> 00:37:32,600
She won't...

427
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:35,270
at least tell me she wants to break up.

428
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:39,880
Hey.

429
00:37:47,250 --> 00:37:48,250
Let's go.

430
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,090
You should sit here.

431
00:37:53,660 --> 00:37:55,360
- Pardon? - We finished our drinks.

432
00:37:56,530 --> 00:37:58,030
- But you didn't. - Have a good day.

433
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:00,030
- Let's go. - Good luck.

434
00:38:00,030 --> 00:38:01,030
Good luck.

435
00:38:07,970 --> 00:38:09,170
What do they mean by that?

436
00:38:09,870 --> 00:38:11,640
They want me to have a busy night.

437
00:38:13,910 --> 00:38:16,050
Is it obvious that I drink a lot?

438
00:38:16,050 --> 00:38:17,150
A bit.

439
00:38:17,980 --> 00:38:20,120
I think I smell alcohol from you too.

440
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:21,150
Really?

