00:40:38,820 --> 00:40:42,690
Most of my customers here are tall and handsome.

482
00:40:43,060 --> 00:40:45,290
But he must stand out among them.

483
00:40:45,630 --> 00:40:47,930
He's a junior law major. His name is Han Jae Hyun.

484
00:40:47,930 --> 00:40:49,870
- I see. Jae Hyun. - When will he come?

485
00:40:50,270 --> 00:40:51,500
I don't know.

486
00:40:53,270 --> 00:40:54,970
Then, what kind of book does he buy?

487
00:42:28,740 --> 00:42:30,180
What a coincidence.

488
00:42:30,850 --> 00:42:32,350
Do you come here often too?

489
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:34,020
- Move. - What?

490
00:42:34,550 --> 00:42:35,820
You're blocking my way.

491
00:42:36,820 --> 00:42:37,820
I see.

492
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:00,740
("Even Birds Leave the World")

493
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,820
Thank you.

494
00:43:13,660 --> 00:43:14,760
See you.

495
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:21,500
- Miss. - Yes?

496
00:43:21,830 --> 00:43:23,670
Jae Hyun told me to give you this.

497
00:43:26,170 --> 00:43:27,500
("The End of That Summer", Poems by Lee Seong Bok)

498
00:43:32,780 --> 00:43:35,710
